41:22.296 --> 41:26.820
The challenge is how to identify what's most important to be saved.

41:30.043 --> 41:33.906
And I don't mean saving in the narrow sense of what a preservation program does.

41:34.122 --> 41:42.331
in order to optimize the life of the medium, or when the medium is at the end of its use life, convert it into another medium.

41:43.392 --> 41:48.558
I'm talking about the much more difficult problem of deciding what should be in the library in the first place.

41:49.539 --> 41:53.183
And then once it's here and it's reached the end of its service life, what should continue?

41:55.566 --> 42:02.053
And I think that's the essence of what we do.

42:03.772 --> 42:10.961
society's most responsible agents for preservation of the human record.

42:11.461 --> 42:12.963
That's a great quote.

42:13.924 --> 42:16.327
I think this is the philosophy we're talking about.

42:16.888 --> 42:19.791
Well, that's what I get excited about in this work.

42:19.811 --> 42:21.213
That's what I get excited about.

42:21.233 --> 42:23.816
That's great.

42:24.197 --> 42:25.378
Excellent.

